WEBVTT

00:06.917 --> 00:08.083
[door opens]

00:10.500 --> 00:12.417
[creaking]

00:21.708 --> 00:23.708
[locks door]

00:25.417 --> 00:28.417
[footsteps moving away]

00:30.000 --> 00:32.000
♪

00:37.375 --> 00:39.375
[rattling]

00:41.875 --> 00:43.875
♪

00:58.792 --> 01:02.583
[dog barking in distance]

01:06.500 --> 01:08.458
NEWS ANCHOR: [on laptop]
<i>Well, when you take a look</i>
<i>at the number of boys</i>

01:08.458 --> 01:10.083
<i>who were hospitalized every year</i>

01:10.083 --> 01:12.167
<i>because they deliberately</i>
<i>harmed themselves,</i>

01:12.625 --> 01:15.167
<i>you'll notice that the numbers</i>
<i>stay relatively the same</i>

01:15.167 --> 01:16.708
<i>until the last decade or so</i>

01:16.708 --> 01:18.792
<i>when there was a sudden,</i>
<i>sharp increase.</i>

01:18.792 --> 01:20.333
<i>And it's getting even worse.</i>

01:20.333 --> 01:22.333
♪

01:40.125 --> 01:42.417
[ominous whispers]

01:42.417 --> 01:43.958
<i>So, what's causing this?</i>

01:43.958 --> 01:45.167
<i>There's no way of knowing for sure,</i>

01:45.167 --> 01:48.458
<i>but it happens to coincide</i>
<i>with the rise of social media</i>

01:48.458 --> 01:51.500
<i>and an increase in screen time</i>
<i>among young people.</i>

01:51.500 --> 01:53.875
<i>So, technology will certainly be--</i>

01:56.625 --> 01:58.458
[wind whooshing]

02:12.333 --> 02:15.208
[insects chirping]

02:19.333 --> 02:22.125
♪

02:22.125 --> 02:23.958
[gasping]

02:23.958 --> 02:25.375
<i>Out of your child's bedroom</i>

02:25.375 --> 02:27.542
<i>for at least an hour</i>
<i>before their bedtime.</i>

02:27.542 --> 02:30.500
<i>There's no reason a child should have</i>
<i>a tablet or a laptop,</i>

02:30.500 --> 02:32.250
<i>or any other thing</i>
<i>for that matter,</i>

02:32.250 --> 02:34.333
<i>in their bedroom</i>
<i>after a certain time.</i>

02:34.333 --> 02:37.333
[news anchor continues]

02:40.167 --> 02:42.167
♪

02:59.458 --> 03:02.458
[door opens]

03:09.625 --> 03:11.625
[door creaking]

03:16.750 --> 03:18.750
♪

03:21.667 --> 03:22.958
[gasps]

03:25.917 --> 03:28.792
- Baby, put the knife down.

03:30.000 --> 03:31.583
Put the knife down, Brandon.

03:32.958 --> 03:34.208
You don't wanna do this, baby.

03:34.208 --> 03:36.375
You don't, you don't wanna
hurt yourself again. Come on.

03:36.792 --> 03:39.750
♪ ominous music playing ♪

03:42.083 --> 03:43.708
Just put the knife down.

03:49.500 --> 03:51.125
[screams]
[grunts]

03:55.667 --> 03:56.958
[blood splatters]

03:57.333 --> 03:58.917
[gasps]

03:58.917 --> 04:00.917
♪

04:08.042 --> 04:10.000
ASHA: [whispering]
<i>Sometimes it doesn't seem fair.</i>

04:13.042 --> 04:15.458
<i>The world is such a beautiful place.</i>

04:17.375 --> 04:21.917
<i>But we're so filled with stress</i>
<i>and anxiety most of the time,</i>

04:22.708 --> 04:24.458
<i>we don't even get to enjoy it.</i>

04:27.625 --> 04:29.625
<i>But I figured out a way</i>

04:29.625 --> 04:32.208
<i>to take the things</i>
<i>that give you stress</i>

04:32.208 --> 04:34.167
<i>and turn them</i>
<i>into something beautiful.</i>

04:35.667 --> 04:37.583
<i>That's what I wanted</i>
<i>to show you guys.</i>

04:38.792 --> 04:42.375
<i>First, make a list</i>
<i>of all the things</i>

04:42.375 --> 04:43.625
<i>that give you stress,</i>

04:44.958 --> 04:46.667
<i>and then for each item,</i>

04:47.333 --> 04:49.958
<i>find an object</i>
<i>that represents that,</i>

04:50.708 --> 04:52.250
<i>something you don't need anymore.</i>

04:52.667 --> 04:54.458
<i>If you're feeling pressure,</i>

04:55.750 --> 04:56.583
<i>like,</i>

04:57.000 --> 05:00.542
maybe you're feeling pressure
to succeed or whatever,

05:01.500 --> 05:04.042
you can find something
that represents that.

05:04.042 --> 05:06.583
Maybe you feel like
no one listens to you.

05:08.542 --> 05:11.875
For that, I've just got
these old headphones

05:11.875 --> 05:13.167
that don't work anymore.

05:14.000 --> 05:16.375
[rubbing]

05:16.958 --> 05:19.417
One you have all your items,

05:19.958 --> 05:21.208
we can take them,

05:22.000 --> 05:25.708
and use them to create relaxing sounds

05:25.708 --> 05:27.417
and images, like so.

05:29.542 --> 05:31.542
[crunching]

05:33.458 --> 05:36.250
[crunching]

05:38.625 --> 05:40.083
[squishing]

05:43.000 --> 05:44.083
[squishing]

05:47.708 --> 05:50.333
[tapping foot]

05:54.583 --> 05:56.708
[foot tapping intensifies]

06:00.208 --> 06:02.750
LEAH: [shouts]
Asha, we're leaving in five!

06:04.042 --> 06:05.250
[chuckles]

06:06.042 --> 06:07.417
Okay, one more, but no faces.

06:07.417 --> 06:08.833
- Alright. Okay.

06:08.833 --> 06:11.542
- Alright, one, two, three.
[camera shutter clicks]

06:11.542 --> 06:13.750
Aww, that's so sweet.

06:14.208 --> 06:15.667
- Hey, I'm proud of you, kiddo.

06:17.792 --> 06:19.375
Ah-ha! There she is.

06:19.375 --> 06:20.958
Alright,

06:21.375 --> 06:23.875
phones on the table, everyone.

06:23.875 --> 06:24.917
Let's go.

06:24.917 --> 06:26.458
- Wait, we're seriously
still doing this?

06:26.458 --> 06:28.000
- Well, we have one
phone-free outing per week.

06:28.000 --> 06:29.333
We haven't had one
this week, so--

06:29.333 --> 06:31.708
- Dad, I swear we're
the only family that does this.

06:31.708 --> 06:32.875
- Oh, really?
You know who else does it?

06:32.875 --> 06:35.292
The people that invented
the technology and the apps

06:35.292 --> 06:36.667
that we're all so addicted to.

06:37.167 --> 06:38.417
- But I'm not addicted.

06:38.417 --> 06:40.167
- Well, then this shouldn't be
a problem for you.

06:44.792 --> 06:46.375
- Let's just-- Honey, let's just
get it over with, okay?

06:46.375 --> 06:48.042
AMIR:
Come on, let's go, out the door.

06:48.042 --> 06:49.667
Let's go.
Thank you very much.

06:49.667 --> 06:51.542
Your phones will be here
waiting for you when you return.

06:51.542 --> 06:52.500
[door opens, closes]

06:52.500 --> 06:55.500
♪ smooth jazz playing ♪

07:12.417 --> 07:14.417
- He's really good.
- I know.

07:15.667 --> 07:17.375
- Other guys look like they're
in high school, though.

07:17.875 --> 07:19.000
- They are. Yeah, yeah.
- Whoa.

07:19.000 --> 07:21.333
- They wanted to play with him
after he won that competition.

07:21.792 --> 07:24.000
I mean, Kamran might
as well be in high school.

07:24.000 --> 07:25.500
His scores are high enough.

07:25.500 --> 07:26.500
He's a great kid.

07:26.500 --> 07:27.458
DAVID: Good for him.
AMIR: Mm-hm.

07:30.750 --> 07:32.625
♪

07:42.292 --> 07:43.208
- Oh.

07:45.333 --> 07:46.375
There they go.

07:47.750 --> 07:49.125
- Don't stress about it, Leah.

07:50.042 --> 07:51.792
Our daughters'
attention spans are shot.

07:52.458 --> 07:54.083
We just have to accept that.

07:59.083 --> 08:00.750
- Are you mad at me?
- What?

08:00.750 --> 08:01.917
No, why would I be mad?

08:01.917 --> 08:03.875
- I sent you, like, five texts
and didn't hear back.

08:04.667 --> 08:07.083
- Sorry, I'm on
a "phone-free outing."

08:07.083 --> 08:09.042
- God, not again.

08:09.042 --> 08:10.667
Well, whatever.
At least I've got mine. Come on.

08:11.667 --> 08:13.000
- Ever since I quit,

08:13.000 --> 08:14.917
they've been doubling down
on the anti-phone thing.

08:14.917 --> 08:16.792
It's, like, all I did was
quit the track team,

08:16.792 --> 08:18.208
but the way they're reacting,

08:18.208 --> 08:21.750
it's like I, I shaved my head
and joined a cult or something.

08:21.750 --> 08:24.667
- Well, at least then you'd be doing
an extracurricular activity.

08:25.250 --> 08:27.250
♪

08:31.250 --> 08:32.458
[cell phone chimes]

08:33.542 --> 08:35.542
- I'm sorry. Sorry.
- It's fine.

08:35.542 --> 08:38.208
- I'm addicted to this
local news app thing.

08:38.667 --> 08:40.500
There's something going around, man.

08:40.500 --> 08:43.208
These two kids in town
cut themselves apparently

08:43.208 --> 08:45.958
because of some internet challenge.

08:46.833 --> 08:47.833
- Cut themselves?

08:47.833 --> 08:51.333
- Yeah, it's like this, um,
scary character that pops up

08:51.333 --> 08:54.750
and tells you to do stuff
like cut yourself,

08:54.750 --> 08:57.792
kill yourself,
or hurt other people.

08:59.917 --> 09:02.167
It even made this kid
stab his own mother.

09:02.167 --> 09:03.500
- What?
- Yeah.

09:03.500 --> 09:05.708
[cell phones chime, buzz]

09:11.000 --> 09:13.000
- Why would they just do
whatever the thing tells them to?

09:13.000 --> 09:14.125
- I don't know, I mean,

09:14.792 --> 09:18.042
if it's trendy, Amir,
kids will do just about anything.

09:18.042 --> 09:19.500
- Boys!
- Sorry.

09:20.125 --> 09:21.125
- Sorry.

09:21.125 --> 09:23.125
♪

09:27.875 --> 09:29.000
- Thirteen views.

09:30.250 --> 09:32.875
I'm up one view, but that's still
10 down from my last video.

09:32.875 --> 09:33.958
- Let me see.

09:36.000 --> 09:36.917
- I don't know,

09:37.625 --> 09:39.542
maybe I'm just not
influencer material.

09:39.958 --> 09:40.833
- Don't give up.

09:41.417 --> 09:43.292
First of all, you need
a way better thumbnail.

09:43.292 --> 09:45.625
This one does not make me
wanna click on it at all.

09:46.500 --> 09:47.625
Oh, hey, you got a comment.

09:51.292 --> 09:53.917
ASHA:
"Wow." Who's Cassidy Johnston?

09:55.083 --> 09:56.667
- Oh no, this is not good.

09:56.667 --> 09:58.083
- Wait, d-do you know her?

09:58.083 --> 09:59.542
- I know that she's, like, evil.

10:00.042 --> 10:01.125
- What do you mean "evil"?

10:01.125 --> 10:02.292
- You know, creepy.

10:02.292 --> 10:03.875
Like, you don't want
to get on her bad side.

10:04.500 --> 10:06.500
- But she liked it. She said, "Wow."

10:06.500 --> 10:08.833
- Asha, nobody says "wow"
in a good way anymore.

10:08.833 --> 10:10.750
People only say "wow" if it's like,

10:11.875 --> 10:13.708
"Wow, really?"

10:13.708 --> 10:15.708
There must've been something
in the video that offended her.

10:15.708 --> 10:17.000
- What? No!
I don't even know her.

10:17.000 --> 10:19.000
♪

10:20.958 --> 10:22.458
[muffled]
What? I don't even know her!

10:23.083 --> 10:25.625
[indistinct conversation]

10:34.417 --> 10:36.292
EMILY: Hey, Mr. Chaudhry.
- Hi, Em.

10:36.292 --> 10:38.542
EMILY:
Uh, we were just headed back inside.

10:39.333 --> 10:40.375
See you in there.

10:42.292 --> 10:43.875
[door opens]

10:44.708 --> 10:45.750
[door closes]

10:47.500 --> 10:49.625
- It's another phone-free outing
down the drain, I guess.

10:49.625 --> 10:51.333
- We were just looking
at my video.

10:52.458 --> 10:54.417
She's helping me get
more traffic to my channel.

10:54.833 --> 10:55.667
- Is that all it was?

10:57.208 --> 10:58.375
- Yeah.

10:59.667 --> 11:02.708
- Look, Asha, I, um, I know, okay?

11:02.708 --> 11:04.500
I know this all seems really silly,

11:04.500 --> 11:06.625
all the phone-free outings,
whatever, it's just,

11:07.750 --> 11:10.792
these are supposed to be some
of the best years of your life, okay?

11:10.792 --> 11:14.583
And I... just don't wanna
see you waste it is all.

11:15.875 --> 11:17.417
- I don't feel like I'm wasting it.

11:18.625 --> 11:22.083
Running in circles for hours
every day after class

11:22.083 --> 11:24.250
until I'm too exhausted
to do anything else,

11:24.250 --> 11:25.208
that's wasting it.

11:26.500 --> 11:27.500
Okay. I mean, like,

11:28.792 --> 11:30.375
I feel like there's
a whole world out there.

11:31.208 --> 11:32.625
- I know, and that's--

11:33.542 --> 11:35.625
I mean, that is what I've been
trying to get you to see.

11:35.625 --> 11:36.500
I--

11:40.750 --> 11:42.125
Okay.

11:42.125 --> 11:44.875
Look, we should, um, we should
get back inside, come on.

11:49.750 --> 11:51.125
KAMRAN:
<i>I'm at 30 health right now,</i>

11:51.125 --> 11:52.292
<i>getting full shield would be ideal.</i>

11:53.667 --> 11:54.667
Contact northwest.

11:54.667 --> 11:56.667
[video game sounds]

11:58.833 --> 12:00.000
Uh, popping minis.

12:03.125 --> 12:04.083
Uh, yeah.

12:04.083 --> 12:05.167
[inaudible]

12:05.167 --> 12:07.833
I'd [laughs] like that a lot.

12:11.875 --> 12:14.875
[Kamran continues talking]

12:19.500 --> 12:20.542
I see his teammate.

12:22.750 --> 12:23.583
Engaging.

12:25.333 --> 12:27.208
Finish. Alright. [inaudible]

12:29.083 --> 12:31.667
♪ light music playing
over headphones ♪

12:41.333 --> 12:42.750
[cell phone chimes]

12:45.708 --> 12:47.125
[phone chimes]

12:51.625 --> 12:54.000
♪ ominous music plays ♪

13:03.542 --> 13:05.292
[paper fluttering]

13:05.958 --> 13:08.625
[door creaking]

13:14.667 --> 13:15.875
- Hello?

13:16.625 --> 13:18.125
[creaking]

13:33.542 --> 13:35.667
- Asha?
[Asha sighs]

13:35.667 --> 13:37.083
Could you come upstairs for a second?

13:37.083 --> 13:38.583
We need to talk to you guys
about something.

13:39.708 --> 13:40.875
He looks like this.

13:43.250 --> 13:45.000
- Wait, what is it called again?

13:45.000 --> 13:47.583
- Grimcutty. You sure
you haven’t seen it before?

13:47.583 --> 13:48.458
- What is it?

13:48.458 --> 13:51.625
- It's, um, some kind
of sick online challenge

13:51.625 --> 13:53.333
that tells you to do stuff like,

13:53.792 --> 13:55.542
I don't know, cut yourself,
choke yourself,

13:56.750 --> 13:57.833
even kill yourself.

13:57.833 --> 13:59.583
- Tells us to do stuff how?

13:59.583 --> 14:00.542
AMIR:
We're not sure exactly.

14:00.542 --> 14:02.583
You know, it could pop up
in the middle of a video,

14:02.583 --> 14:06.458
or be a link that you click on,
or even personal messages.

14:06.458 --> 14:08.833
The point is
is that it's working, okay?

14:09.500 --> 14:12.125
Couple of local kids already
cut themselves because of it.

14:12.125 --> 14:13.875
It even made one kid stab his mom.

14:14.333 --> 14:16.667
- Maybe it's like subliminal messages
that flash so fast

14:16.667 --> 14:18.917
you don't even know you saw 'em,
like MK Ultra!

14:18.917 --> 14:20.167
- Kamran, we're being serious
right now, honey.

14:20.167 --> 14:21.042
- Yeah.
ASHA: I don't get it.

14:21.042 --> 14:22.583
Why would anyone do that, though?

14:22.583 --> 14:25.375
- On a dare, maybe.
You know, or to get attention.

14:25.375 --> 14:27.500
- You think we're gonna
cut ourselves for attention?

14:27.500 --> 14:29.000
- Well, you wouldn't think
that somebody would lick

14:29.000 --> 14:30.125
an armrest on an airplane

14:30.125 --> 14:32.500
or climb a tower of milk crates
to get attention,

14:32.500 --> 14:33.333
but they did that.

14:33.333 --> 14:34.458
- Okay, well, we didn't.

14:34.458 --> 14:36.292
- We know that.
- Yeah.

14:36.292 --> 14:38.792
I'm-- Look, all we're saying is that

14:39.625 --> 14:41.667
we just want you guys
to be aware of it, okay?

14:41.667 --> 14:45.208
We know that you like
to look at stuff online.

14:45.208 --> 14:46.833
We're gonna respect your privacy.

14:47.958 --> 14:52.417
Just... please don't do
anything stupid, okay?

14:52.958 --> 14:55.625
- Dad, I think you can relax.

14:55.625 --> 14:57.208
We're not gonna stab you.

15:12.208 --> 15:14.625
<i>- If someone has a link</i>
<i>to the Grimcutty challenge</i>

15:14.625 --> 15:16.333
<i>will you please post it?</i>

15:16.333 --> 15:18.208
<i>I will pay money.</i>

15:18.208 --> 15:19.125
[phone buzzes]

15:24.292 --> 15:26.292
♪

15:26.292 --> 15:29.333
[typing on cell phone]

15:46.042 --> 15:47.542
- We're just overreacting, right, honey?

15:47.542 --> 15:50.083
I mean, she's--
Asha's into weird stuff,

15:50.083 --> 15:52.917
but she's not crazy enough
to do something like that, right?

15:53.875 --> 15:54.792
- Sure.

15:55.875 --> 15:57.292
[cell phone buzzes]

15:59.625 --> 16:00.417
What the fuck?

16:01.875 --> 16:02.708
- What is it?

16:03.167 --> 16:06.125
- Linda said Karen and Phil just caught
Madison in the hallway cutting herself.

16:06.542 --> 16:07.792
- Because of Grimcutty?

16:08.625 --> 16:09.625
- Didn't say.

16:11.875 --> 16:15.292
- Okay, I don't-- I mean, this just--
It can't, it can't be, uh--

16:15.292 --> 16:16.250
This just--

16:21.167 --> 16:22.375
You know,
we should do more research.

16:22.375 --> 16:24.333
- Yeah.
AMIR: Yeah, let's--

16:28.042 --> 16:29.083
Just, uh--

16:30.917 --> 16:34.583
[crackling]
[ominous whispers]

16:50.500 --> 16:51.875
[sighs]

16:51.875 --> 16:53.917
[rustling]

16:54.875 --> 16:57.958
PERSON: [over earphones]
<i>But they're very, very soft.</i>

16:57.958 --> 16:59.958
[rustling]

17:15.917 --> 17:17.125
[toaster pops]

17:24.333 --> 17:25.833
[knife scraping]

17:28.792 --> 17:31.708
[rustling continues]

17:31.708 --> 17:33.292
[typing]

17:33.292 --> 17:34.625
[scraping]

17:34.625 --> 17:36.625
[rustling]

17:44.708 --> 17:48.417
[scraping]

17:48.417 --> 17:51.417
♪ ominous music plays ♪

17:53.667 --> 17:54.292
[knife clatters]

17:56.792 --> 17:58.208
[screams]

17:59.375 --> 18:00.917
- Jesus.
ASHA: [screams] Dad!

18:01.958 --> 18:03.083
- What?
- Dad!

18:03.083 --> 18:03.833
[clatters]

18:03.833 --> 18:05.708
There's, There's someone in the house!
There's someone in the house!

18:06.375 --> 18:08.000
- We-- Are you alright?

18:08.000 --> 18:09.042
- It was right there.

18:20.833 --> 18:22.417
He was tall.

18:23.167 --> 18:25.333
Like, really, really tall.
And, um,

18:26.917 --> 18:29.458
he was wearing black, like,
I, I wanna say leather.

18:31.333 --> 18:35.125
But, um... his hands were, like, huge.

18:35.125 --> 18:39.583
And... his face,
he had, like, big red eyes.

18:39.583 --> 18:40.750
- Kinda like this?

18:42.500 --> 18:44.917
- Yeah. Like, like that.

18:44.917 --> 18:46.333
OFFICER:
Thought so.

18:46.333 --> 18:47.875
We've been getting calls
about it all night.

18:48.458 --> 18:50.458
- Okay, then somebody
dressed up as Grimcutty

18:50.458 --> 18:51.667
is playing a prank on me.

18:52.292 --> 18:53.542
- Is that possible?

18:53.542 --> 18:56.167
- If that's the case,
it'd have to be a group of people.

18:56.167 --> 18:58.375
One guy couldn't move around that fast.

18:58.375 --> 18:59.917
- What did I see, then?

18:59.917 --> 19:01.125
I mean, you're the cop.

19:01.125 --> 19:02.125
- Asha.

19:03.000 --> 19:05.500
- You remember what you were
doing right before you saw it?

19:06.417 --> 19:07.917
- I was making toast

19:09.542 --> 19:11.083
and watching a video on my phone.

19:18.167 --> 19:20.042
- Do you mind if I talk
to your parents for a minute?

19:23.875 --> 19:25.458
I'm having a really hard time buying

19:25.458 --> 19:27.875
that there's some person out there

19:27.875 --> 19:29.625
making these kids--

19:29.625 --> 19:31.250
- But why?
Why, Why would they lie?

19:31.250 --> 19:32.792
Why would they make this up?

19:32.792 --> 19:34.750
- Maybe it's telling them to lie.

19:34.750 --> 19:36.500
Like, as part of the challenge.

19:37.167 --> 19:39.375
There's still a lot
we don't know about it.

19:39.375 --> 19:40.500
AMIR:
Well, thank you.

19:41.542 --> 19:42.708
Okay, I'll show you out.

19:42.708 --> 19:43.833
Thank you so much.
OFFICER: Thank you.

19:54.875 --> 19:55.958
- What?

19:57.458 --> 19:59.083
- You better let me
hold on to that for now.

19:59.667 --> 20:01.833
- What for?
Dad, what are you doing?

20:01.833 --> 20:04.292
- Just a precaution until we figure out
what the heck is going on.

20:04.292 --> 20:05.500
- Dad, stop it!

20:05.500 --> 20:07.250
You don't seriously think
I'm making this up

20:07.250 --> 20:08.458
because of some online challenge?

20:08.458 --> 20:09.708
- Asha, let go.
- Dad, that's--

20:16.417 --> 20:18.083
LEAH:
You're gonna get it back tomorrow.

20:18.667 --> 20:19.875
We just need to sleep.

20:21.125 --> 20:22.875
Okay? You should try
to get some sleep, too.

20:29.167 --> 20:31.167
[birds chirping]

20:51.333 --> 20:53.583
KAMRAN:
11, 12. I was--

20:53.583 --> 20:55.625
Everything last night was just

20:56.500 --> 20:57.417
a lot.

20:58.708 --> 21:01.208
- Here she is.
Why don't you come join us?

21:14.792 --> 21:16.458
You wanna start?
- Uh, uh, yes, sure.

21:16.917 --> 21:21.500
Um, so, we've been doing these
phone-free outings for a while now, okay,

21:21.500 --> 21:22.833
and you guys have been great.

21:22.833 --> 21:25.333
But we just thought that, you know,
with everything that's been happening,

21:25.333 --> 21:27.292
now might be a really great time

21:27.292 --> 21:30.083
for us to up our game a little bit, okay?

21:30.083 --> 21:31.958
So, we've got this new Detox Box--

21:33.042 --> 21:34.208
- I'm s-- The what?

21:34.208 --> 21:36.167
AMIR:
So, we take all of our devices,

21:36.667 --> 21:38.875
we put 'em in there, we lock it up.

21:38.875 --> 21:41.458
And then, in a week,
we see how we're feeling,

21:41.458 --> 21:43.375
and we decide if we even
wanna keep going.

21:46.875 --> 21:49.750
- I have so many questions.
- That's what we're here for.

21:49.750 --> 21:50.625
Shoot
- Uh-huh.

21:50.625 --> 21:52.250
- Okay, how 'bout why?

21:54.500 --> 21:56.083
- Well, because, um,

21:56.500 --> 21:58.708
clearly, these devices
are affecting you guys

21:58.708 --> 22:00.792
in ways that we don't
entirely understand yet,

22:00.792 --> 22:02.417
so really, we're just--

22:02.417 --> 22:03.417
- It's an experiment.

22:03.417 --> 22:04.958
- Exactly.
- Mm-hm. Yeah.

22:04.958 --> 22:06.542
I mean, it may not
make a difference at all,

22:06.542 --> 22:08.667
but we won't know unless we try.

22:09.500 --> 22:10.667
- Can I go first, Dad?

22:10.667 --> 22:12.250
AMIR:
Yes, of course.

22:18.000 --> 22:20.458
Great job.
KAMRAN: Thanks, Dad. Thanks, Mom.

22:20.458 --> 22:22.458
- Alright, thank you.

22:23.167 --> 22:24.000
Okay.

22:30.208 --> 22:32.625
- Please tell me this isn't
because of Grimcutty.

22:34.542 --> 22:36.458
Do you even know what
the Grimcutty challenge is?

22:36.458 --> 22:39.375
Or did you just see that photo
and hear a bunch of rumors about it?

22:39.375 --> 22:41.250
'Cause, you know,
I'd really like to know.

22:41.250 --> 22:44.208
- Sweetie, all we know is that
ever since you quit track,

22:44.208 --> 22:47.417
you have become more
and more withdrawn, okay?

22:47.417 --> 22:49.208
And it's common
for depressed people to have--

22:49.208 --> 22:50.583
- But, But I'm not depressed!

22:50.583 --> 22:52.917
- Look, we have no idea
how these devices are affecting you,

22:52.917 --> 22:54.167
but that is the whole point of this.

22:54.167 --> 22:57.042
So, that you can reclaim your focus game.

22:57.042 --> 22:59.125
- And cut your screen time
in the meantime.

22:59.125 --> 23:00.042
AMIR:
Yeah.

23:00.833 --> 23:02.875
- Okay, what did you guys smoke
while I was asleep?

23:02.875 --> 23:04.667
- Look, we're all doing this, okay?
Put your phone in the box.

23:04.667 --> 23:05.500
- No!

23:06.750 --> 23:10.208
I'm not letting you guys blame this
on phones or anxiety or whatever.

23:10.208 --> 23:11.625
I know what I saw.

23:11.625 --> 23:14.833
It wasn't a hallucination.
It wasn't some guy in a costume.

23:14.833 --> 23:16.792
It was a real thing.
It was huge and terrifying.

23:16.792 --> 23:18.583
I need you guys to help me
figure out what it was!

23:18.583 --> 23:20.625
- Enough, Asha!
- Put your phone in the box!

23:20.625 --> 23:21.708
Now!

23:26.292 --> 23:29.625
- Asha, hey! Let go, Asha.
- I just wanna call Emily.

23:29.625 --> 23:31.167
LEAH: Asha, let go.
- Let go, Asha.

23:31.167 --> 23:33.333
- No, I'll give it back after, I promise!
I just--

23:33.958 --> 23:35.958
[screams]

23:48.958 --> 23:50.958
[panting]

24:01.792 --> 24:02.792
Shh.

24:03.792 --> 24:05.333
I wanna use the laptop.

24:06.458 --> 24:07.458
- What laptop?

24:07.875 --> 24:09.958
- [mocking]
"Can I go first, Dad?"

24:10.792 --> 24:12.167
The golden boy act
doesn't work on me.

24:12.167 --> 24:13.417
I know you have a backup.

24:13.417 --> 24:15.500
Now give it to me.
Unless you want me to tell dad.

24:23.083 --> 24:24.708
- What are you gonna do with it?

24:25.125 --> 24:25.958
[typing]

24:25.958 --> 24:28.583
I already spent hours looking.
You're not gonna find it.

24:29.000 --> 24:31.833
- Like, what about message boards?
Nobody posted a link to it?

24:31.833 --> 24:34.292
- No, there's a lot of people
freaking out about it,

24:34.292 --> 24:36.250
but nobody knows
what it actually is.

24:39.250 --> 24:40.208
What are you doing?

24:41.625 --> 24:42.958
- Where is everybody?

24:45.333 --> 24:46.875
KAMRAN:
I already tried to Skype Zach.

24:47.333 --> 24:49.375
They probably got
their stuff taken away, too.

24:50.750 --> 24:52.500
[humming]

24:55.167 --> 24:56.250
ASHA:
Wait, what the hell?

24:57.000 --> 24:58.083
[footsteps thumping]

24:58.083 --> 24:59.875
LEAH: [muffled]
Did you change the WiFi password?

24:59.875 --> 25:01.375
AMIR: [muffled]
I disconnected it.

25:02.500 --> 25:03.958
- Do you think they know we're--
- Shh!

25:03.958 --> 25:06.917
[indiscernible conversation]

25:16.167 --> 25:17.417
- What are you gonna do?

25:19.542 --> 25:22.875
[clock ticking]

25:36.292 --> 25:39.292
♪ tense music playing ♪

25:59.250 --> 26:00.458
[grunts]

26:05.292 --> 26:07.292
♪

26:29.792 --> 26:32.000
♪

26:41.000 --> 26:42.208
[ringing]

26:42.208 --> 26:43.083
[gasps]

26:46.750 --> 26:48.167
[ringing stops]

26:48.167 --> 26:50.167
[phone buzzing]

26:55.417 --> 26:57.625
<i>- Ashmsauce229.</i>

26:58.625 --> 27:00.417
- Hi.
CASSIDY: <i>Saw your message.</i>

27:01.167 --> 27:03.333
<i>I was worried I was the only one left</i>
<i>that still had a phone.</i>

27:03.333 --> 27:06.875
- No, I just, I just got mine back.
How do you still have yours?

27:06.875 --> 27:09.083
<i>- My parents aren't on</i>
<i>the Grimcutty freakout train yet.</i>

27:09.083 --> 27:11.750
<i>But I'm not gonna give up my phone.</i>

27:11.750 --> 27:13.917
<i>They can't just take our phones away.</i>
<i>That's fascist.</i>

27:14.375 --> 27:15.708
<i>We'll go to the police if we have to.</i>

27:15.708 --> 27:17.917
- No, um, I don't think that's gonna work.

27:17.917 --> 27:20.042
They didn't believe me
any more than my parents did.

27:20.042 --> 27:21.375
<i>- Wh-What do you mean?</i>

27:22.333 --> 27:23.667
<i>You saw the Grimcutty?</i>

27:24.750 --> 27:25.833
- I think so.

27:25.833 --> 27:28.000
<i>- Well, what is it?</i>
<i>Wait, can you send me the link?</i>

27:28.000 --> 27:29.792
<i>You're the first person I've found</i>
<i>that's actually seen it.</i>

27:29.792 --> 27:32.958
- No, I mean, like, I saw it,
or something like it,

27:32.958 --> 27:35.333
like, in, in real life, in my house.

27:38.167 --> 27:39.417
<i>- Okay, that's new.</i>

27:39.417 --> 27:40.792
[door opens, closes]

27:43.750 --> 27:45.750
♪

27:57.417 --> 27:58.417
- What?

27:59.417 --> 28:00.667
- I thought I heard something.

28:03.458 --> 28:05.458
♪

28:15.583 --> 28:17.000
[sighs]

28:21.167 --> 28:22.583
CASSIDY:
<i>What are you doing?</i>

28:23.083 --> 28:24.750
- [whispering]
I can't really talk right now.

28:24.750 --> 28:27.375
CASSIDY:
<i>Well, whatever. Just stay on the line.</i>

28:27.375 --> 28:29.000
<i>I think I might've found someone else.</i>

28:29.667 --> 28:31.417
<i>Gonna try to add them.</i>

28:31.417 --> 28:32.417
<i>Hold on.</i>

28:36.333 --> 28:38.750
[footsteps approaching]

28:48.708 --> 28:50.708
KAYLA: [over phone]
<i>Did you guys hear about Nathan?</i>

28:50.708 --> 28:51.917
CASSIDY:
<i>Who?</i>

28:51.917 --> 28:54.750
<i>- Nathan Childers cut himself,</i>
<i>apparently 'cause of Grimcutty.</i>

28:55.292 --> 28:56.833
<i>And Hannah's little brother</i>
<i>cut himself, too.</i>

28:56.833 --> 29:00.167
<i>It's no joke.</i>
<i>It's really making people do stuff.</i>

29:00.167 --> 29:01.875
CASSIDY:
<i>Well, Asha here has seen it.</i>

29:02.417 --> 29:04.542
<i>- You did? Can you send me the link?</i>

29:04.542 --> 29:06.792
CASSIDY:
<i>No, she saw, like, a ghost or something.</i>

29:10.708 --> 29:12.292
- [whispering]
I don't know what I saw, okay?

29:12.292 --> 29:14.000
The point is
it's not online.

29:14.000 --> 29:15.708
My parents keep saying
some online challenge,

29:15.708 --> 29:17.417
but all I've seen is that stupid picture.

29:18.750 --> 29:21.167
CASSIDY:
<i>Well, the hysteria about it</i>
<i>sure spread fast.</i>

29:21.667 --> 29:24.375
KAYLA:
<i>Heard some parents are even</i>
<i>pulling their kids out of school.</i>

29:24.375 --> 29:25.583
[knocks on door]

29:26.458 --> 29:27.667
- Hold on a second, you guys.

29:30.417 --> 29:32.417
- Sorry, didn't mean
to interrupt your reading.

29:33.167 --> 29:34.917
- Oh, it's okay. What's up?

29:35.833 --> 29:38.500
- We wanna talk to you
about something.

29:38.958 --> 29:40.750
Can you come downstairs
for a minute?

29:40.750 --> 29:41.750
- I'll be right down.

29:46.167 --> 29:47.083
[door closes]

29:47.625 --> 29:51.167
I gotta go. I think I'm about
to get the Grimcutty talk.

29:51.167 --> 29:52.625
<i>- I have to go, too.</i>

29:52.625 --> 29:53.542
CASSIDY:
<i>Alright.</i>

29:54.125 --> 29:56.625
<i>Listen, no matter what,</i>

29:56.625 --> 29:59.292
<i>don't let your parents keep you home</i>
<i>from school tomorrow.</i>

29:59.292 --> 30:00.833
<i>Tell them that you have a test.</i>

30:00.833 --> 30:04.667
<i>Tell them that you love</i>
<i>learning, whatever. Just--</i>

30:05.417 --> 30:06.375
<i>We'll meet up there.</i>

30:06.833 --> 30:07.833
KAYLA:
<i>Okay.</i>

30:08.542 --> 30:09.542
[call ends]

30:11.750 --> 30:13.083
- Hey, did you find her?

30:13.083 --> 30:14.583
- No, did you?
- No.

30:20.000 --> 30:22.000
[heavy breathing]

30:24.875 --> 30:26.875
[ominous whispers]

30:31.000 --> 30:33.000
[soft growl]

30:42.208 --> 30:43.833
[snarls]

30:47.000 --> 30:48.000
[screams]

30:51.542 --> 30:53.542
[screaming]

31:01.708 --> 31:03.125
[growls]

31:04.625 --> 31:07.042
[thudding on door]

31:08.292 --> 31:11.125
[indistinct shouting]

31:11.125 --> 31:15.333
ASHA: Let me go! Let me go!
AMIR: Asha, Asha, Asha!

31:15.333 --> 31:17.000
[indiscernible shouting]

31:19.625 --> 31:20.625
- It's okay.

31:20.625 --> 31:22.625
[heavy breathing]

31:29.917 --> 31:31.333
Is she gonna need stitches?

31:34.250 --> 31:35.458
- I don't think so.

31:40.167 --> 31:41.583
- I didn't do this to myself.

31:44.208 --> 31:45.458
- We should probably
get it looked at, though.

31:45.458 --> 31:46.833
I can bring her in the morning.

31:48.083 --> 31:49.250
- Eh, what about school?

31:49.875 --> 31:50.958
- Don't worry about it.

31:52.292 --> 31:53.458
- But I, I wanna go.

31:55.583 --> 31:56.708
I have a test.

31:56.708 --> 31:58.208
- No, not until we get this figured out.

32:01.792 --> 32:04.125
- D-Do you even care
about my side of the story?

32:05.583 --> 32:06.708
This was an accident.

32:12.125 --> 32:15.083
I used the knife to pry open
the box to get my phone,

32:15.083 --> 32:18.625
and then, I got really spooked
when I heard you guys coming

32:18.625 --> 32:19.833
because of what happened last night.

32:19.833 --> 32:22.875
And so, I ran downstairs,
and then I slammed the door

32:22.875 --> 32:24.417
and then I accidentally cut myself.

32:26.542 --> 32:27.375
That's it.

32:28.208 --> 32:29.958
That's all. I didn't,
I didn't do it on purpose.

32:29.958 --> 32:32.208
I didn't do it
'cause Grimcutty told me to.

32:36.542 --> 32:38.875
Okay, look, I don't, I don't know
what I saw last night.

32:39.958 --> 32:42.333
But I just really want things
to go back to normal.

32:43.125 --> 32:46.542
And I feel like going back to school
would really make me feel normal.

32:49.667 --> 32:52.625
Please, I just--
I feel like school's the right--

32:53.292 --> 32:54.708
is the right place for me.

32:58.792 --> 32:59.750
- Maybe she should go.

32:59.750 --> 33:00.833
- No, it's out of the question.

33:00.833 --> 33:04.083
- Okay, well, then do you wanna stay home
from work and watch her all day?

33:04.083 --> 33:04.917
- I can't--

33:04.917 --> 33:06.625
LEAH:
She wants to go to school,
let her go to school.

33:06.625 --> 33:07.875
She has supervision there.

33:07.875 --> 33:09.875
AMIR:
Okay, well, then this is on you, alright?

33:10.583 --> 33:13.583
- Can I talk to you upstairs for just--
AMIR: Why?

33:18.417 --> 33:19.417
What did I do this time?

33:21.583 --> 33:23.417
[indiscernible conversation]

33:23.417 --> 33:25.083
[creaking]

33:31.833 --> 33:33.042
PRINCIPAL: [on mic]
<i>Good morning, everyone.</i>

33:34.125 --> 33:35.583
<i>As you can see,</i>

33:36.042 --> 33:39.333
<i>some of you have chosen</i>
<i>to stay home today</i>

33:39.333 --> 33:41.875
<i>given what's been happening.</i>

33:42.542 --> 33:45.083
<i>Some of you have already talked</i>
<i>to your parents about it,</i>

33:46.125 --> 33:48.333
<i>the rest of you probably will later.</i>

33:49.417 --> 33:51.750
<i>But since we're here,</i>
<i>we want you to know</i>

33:51.750 --> 33:55.083
<i>that this is a place where</i>
<i>you can be completely open</i>

33:55.083 --> 33:57.458
<i>about... social media,</i>

33:58.292 --> 33:59.333
<i>bullying,</i>

33:59.833 --> 34:00.833
<i>FOMO,</i>

34:01.792 --> 34:05.333
<i>these online challenges that are becoming</i>
<i>more and more dangerous--</i>

34:05.333 --> 34:06.875
- This is bullshit!

34:06.875 --> 34:09.917
It's just a scary picture!
That's all that it is! It's just hype!

34:09.917 --> 34:12.125
It's all BS!
We're not in any danger!

34:12.125 --> 34:13.667
Oh my--

34:13.667 --> 34:18.542
<i>- Okay, um, obviously</i>
<i>some intense emotions.</i>
[door opens, closes]

34:18.542 --> 34:22.917
<i>Which is why we're here,</i>
<i>to get everything out into the open.</i>

34:24.000 --> 34:27.042
<i>Now, we are gonna take questions later,</i>
<i>but before we get into that,</i>

34:27.042 --> 34:30.833
<i>uh, we have managed to get</i>
<i>a very special guest,</i>

34:30.833 --> 34:33.833
<i>who I think can shed some light,</i>
<i>and some humor,</i>

34:33.833 --> 34:35.458
<i>on this situation,</i>

34:35.458 --> 34:38.542
<i>which I think we could all use.</i>

34:39.250 --> 34:41.875
<i>He travels across the country</i>
<i>talking to teens</i>

34:41.875 --> 34:45.417
<i>about the ups and downs of social media.</i>

34:45.417 --> 34:48.500
<i>Please give a hand</i>
<i>for Dave Bagliardi!</i>

34:48.500 --> 34:52.125
<i>- Woo! Alright, how we all</i>
<i>doin' this morning?!</i>

34:52.625 --> 34:54.833
<i>Okay, okay. I get it. I get it.</i>

34:54.833 --> 34:56.542
<i>It's early. I know how it is.</i>

34:56.542 --> 34:59.542
<i>You haven't had your Starbucks yet.</i>
<i>I feel you. Boy, do I feel you.</i>

34:59.542 --> 35:02.917
<i>But I think we can do</i>
<i>a little bit better than that.</i>

35:02.917 --> 35:05.667
<i>So, how y'all doin' this morning?</i>

35:05.667 --> 35:07.083
[scattered applause]

35:07.083 --> 35:09.125
<i>Okay, okay.</i>

35:09.125 --> 35:11.500
<i>Not bad, not bad.</i>
<i>I can work with that.</i>

35:12.083 --> 35:14.042
<i>Good morning, everyone.</i>
<i>It's good to see you.</i>

35:14.042 --> 35:15.583
<i>As your lovely principal mentioned,</i>

35:15.583 --> 35:17.208
<i>my name is Dave Bagliardi.</i>

35:17.208 --> 35:19.375
<i>And before we get started here today,</i>

35:19.375 --> 35:20.958
<i>I wanna tell you all a little story.</i>

35:20.958 --> 35:23.125
<i>Wayyy back when</i>
<i>when I was in high school,</i>

35:23.125 --> 35:25.417
<i>things were a lot different.</i>

35:25.417 --> 35:27.708
<i>And I know you're</i>
<i>probably asking yourself,</i>

35:27.708 --> 35:29.292
<i>"What does this old geezer know</i>

35:29.292 --> 35:31.833
<i>about anything that is</i>
<i>going on with me, right?"</i>

35:35.625 --> 35:37.250
- Hey, is your friend coming?

35:37.250 --> 35:38.750
- Kay didn't make it.

35:38.750 --> 35:40.167
None of my friends did.

35:40.167 --> 35:42.125
- Do you still have your phone?
- No.

35:42.125 --> 35:43.958
My parents got to me
after you hung up.

35:43.958 --> 35:46.458
They made me put it
in a "Detox Box."

35:46.458 --> 35:49.250
- My parents said the same thing.

35:49.250 --> 35:51.208
They used that exact term?
- Yeah.

35:51.208 --> 35:53.625
They said it was
to "reclaim my focus game

35:53.625 --> 35:56.625
and cut my screen time in the meantime."
- "Your screen time in the meantime."

35:57.958 --> 35:59.375
Where are they getting this?

35:59.375 --> 36:01.667
It's like they're reading
from the same script.

36:01.667 --> 36:03.667
- I don't know. It's weird.

36:06.750 --> 36:08.167
Do I even wanna know?

36:09.583 --> 36:11.417
- Unless you've seen it,
I doubt you'll believe me.

36:11.958 --> 36:14.375
- Well, I haven't, but

36:14.917 --> 36:17.667
I just wanna know what's
brainwashing my parents.

36:18.042 --> 36:20.042
And I want my phone back.

36:20.042 --> 36:21.583
I can't fall asleep without Bob Ross.

36:22.708 --> 36:23.917
- Me neither.

36:28.458 --> 36:31.083
- Alright then, Ashmsauce.

36:32.000 --> 36:33.000
What do we do first?

36:33.500 --> 36:36.333
- If I could just use the internet
for, like, five seconds.

36:36.333 --> 36:37.500
- What about the computers
in the library?

36:37.500 --> 36:39.042
- Disconnected. I already checked.

36:40.125 --> 36:41.333
- Um.

36:42.917 --> 36:44.917
[chuckles]
Alright.

36:45.458 --> 36:47.875
I know someone who will
definitely let us use their computer.

36:50.375 --> 36:51.375
Come on.

36:51.958 --> 36:53.583
[door opens]
I'll drive.

36:54.958 --> 36:56.958
♪ hip-hop music playing ♪

36:56.958 --> 36:59.792
ASHA: Whose house is this again?
CASSIDY: This rich kid, Oliver.

36:59.792 --> 37:01.292
Heard he was having a ditch party.

37:01.792 --> 37:03.333
Looks like I was right.

37:03.333 --> 37:04.583
ASHA:
Won't his parents be home?

37:05.167 --> 37:08.000
CASSIDY:
Fuck no. They work in, like,
international shipping or something,

37:08.000 --> 37:09.417
and they're hardly ever home.

37:09.417 --> 37:10.917
Practically lives by himself.

37:12.083 --> 37:13.292
[doorbell rings]

37:13.792 --> 37:15.000
- Were you even invited?

37:16.792 --> 37:19.375
- We're girls. I don't think
he'll care how we got here.

37:19.708 --> 37:21.750
Besides, he's a really big fan
of your channel.

37:21.750 --> 37:22.375
- What?!

37:22.375 --> 37:24.792
- Yeah, he's the one who told me about it.

37:27.375 --> 37:29.500
[laughs]

37:29.500 --> 37:30.708
I'm kidding!

37:31.750 --> 37:33.375
You know, for someone
who makes ASMR videos,

37:33.375 --> 37:34.458
you're a little tense.

37:35.042 --> 37:36.458
[buzzer sounds, door opens]

37:36.458 --> 37:39.083
♪ hip-hop music intensifies ♪

37:39.083 --> 37:41.083
[people chattering]

37:43.375 --> 37:45.375
♪

37:54.000 --> 37:55.542
CASSIDY:
Hey, Oliver.

37:55.542 --> 38:00.167
- Hey, Cassidy! Hey... you guys.
Come in. Come in. Come in.

38:00.167 --> 38:02.125
Help yourself to whatever.

38:02.125 --> 38:05.667
- Actually, do you have a laptop
that we could use?

38:05.667 --> 38:08.417
- Uh, the WiFi password is
on the wall in there.

38:08.417 --> 38:10.417
- We--
[blender whirring]

38:15.542 --> 38:16.958
- We don't have phones.

38:18.542 --> 38:20.958
- Oh shit! 'Cause of Grimcutty?

38:22.167 --> 38:26.792
Wow, that is... fascist.
Uh... yeah, sure.

38:28.083 --> 38:29.292
Come on, you can use mine.

38:31.250 --> 38:34.333
So, your parents got
the Grimcutty hysteria, huh?

38:34.333 --> 38:36.458
I feel for you, man,
but we don't care about that here.

38:36.458 --> 38:39.208
- I don't suppose you know
what the Grimcutty actually is?

38:39.208 --> 38:40.417
- What do you mean?

38:40.417 --> 38:43.292
- I mean what it is that's
making people cut themselves.

38:43.292 --> 38:46.250
Is it just some asshole sending people
messages on WhatsApp?

38:46.250 --> 38:48.375
- Look all I know is it's the reason

38:48.375 --> 38:50.167
we don't have to go to school
if we don't want to,

38:50.167 --> 38:51.875
so that is what we're celebrating.

38:51.875 --> 38:53.708
- Wait, wait, wait. I have an idea.

38:54.208 --> 38:55.417
Everyone,

38:56.042 --> 38:57.250
take out your knives!

38:57.958 --> 38:58.792
When I hit record,

38:58.792 --> 39:01.000
I want everyone
to start, uh, pretending

39:01.000 --> 39:02.583
like they're brainwashed
by Grimcutty, okay?

39:02.583 --> 39:04.083
[laughter]

39:04.083 --> 39:06.083
Three, two, one.

39:06.083 --> 39:09.958
Gah!
- Grimcutty. Grimcutty.

39:09.958 --> 39:13.750
ALL:
Grimcutty!

39:13.750 --> 39:15.667
[laughter]

39:19.292 --> 39:20.708
- Aren't your parents gonna see that?

39:20.708 --> 39:23.375
- My parents? No.
They're in Morocco or something.

39:23.375 --> 39:25.625
♪ hip-hop music playing ♪

39:26.000 --> 39:28.000
Just boot it up
for you real quick.

39:29.458 --> 39:31.458
[typing]

39:33.667 --> 39:34.875
There you go.
[woman moans]

39:34.875 --> 39:36.500
Oh! Um--

39:37.208 --> 39:41.042
That wasn't-- That's... school, um--

39:43.000 --> 39:44.000
There you go.

39:48.917 --> 39:50.333
- Do I even wanna touch this keyboard?

39:50.333 --> 39:53.083
- Just... do a search for "Detox Box,"

39:53.083 --> 39:54.083
see what comes up.

39:58.875 --> 40:03.083
- Fran, I ordered a breathing treatment
for the guy that's in room two.

40:03.083 --> 40:04.083
[Nicholas groans]

40:04.083 --> 40:06.083
- Let go of me, man! Get off me!

40:07.458 --> 40:08.458
This is bullshit!

40:08.458 --> 40:10.667
- Another one of those kids
who played that cutting game.

40:10.667 --> 40:13.083
You know, on the internet
with that scary guy?

40:13.917 --> 40:15.125
[door closes]

40:15.125 --> 40:17.542
Your kids aren't into
that kind of stuff, are they?

40:18.375 --> 40:20.208
- Uh, no. Thank god.

40:21.000 --> 40:23.583
- All I can say is,
thank god I don't have kids.

40:23.583 --> 40:26.167
[cell phone chimes, buzzes]

40:26.167 --> 40:28.167
- Hey.
- Hey, I just got to the school.

40:28.167 --> 40:29.375
She's not here.

40:29.375 --> 40:31.083
<i>We should never have</i>
<i>let her leave the house.</i>

40:31.083 --> 40:33.333
- Okay, calm down, calm down.
D-- Are you sure she didn't go home?

40:33.333 --> 40:36.167
- Well, I'm headed home now.
Get there when you can.

40:36.167 --> 40:37.083
[call ends]

40:37.083 --> 40:37.958
- Oh god.

40:38.750 --> 40:40.583
♪ hip-hop music continues ♪

40:40.583 --> 40:41.792
- Wait, click on that.

40:50.083 --> 40:51.708
ASHA:
Looks like a mommy blogger.

40:56.125 --> 40:57.333
"Hi, I'm Melinda.

40:57.958 --> 41:00.958
"Years ago, I began a journey
that would change my life forever.

41:01.458 --> 41:02.875
A journey called motherhood."

41:04.208 --> 41:05.625
- Wait, go back to the post.

41:08.417 --> 41:11.417
- "Is your child's smart phone
making them grow horns?"

41:11.417 --> 41:15.208
- "Ear infections:
Is your 5G network to blame?"

41:15.208 --> 41:19.417
- "My son is never bored.
Here's why that's a problem."

41:22.542 --> 41:24.542
Oh my god, no way.

41:26.417 --> 41:28.042
CASSIDY:
That bitch!

41:32.000 --> 41:35.000
- "Cut your screen time in the meantime."

41:36.000 --> 41:37.625
- Anything about Grimcutty?

41:42.417 --> 41:43.625
Does it say what it is?

41:48.625 --> 41:50.250
Oh.
- She took it down.

41:50.750 --> 41:52.958
But whatever. I think it’s obvious
she’s hiding something.

41:53.583 --> 41:56.000
- Hey, did you hear about that kid in town

41:56.000 --> 41:57.333
that stabbed his mom?
- Mm-hm.

41:58.583 --> 42:00.792
- Well, how much you wanna bet that's her?

42:01.875 --> 42:02.708
- How do you know?

42:03.167 --> 42:05.583
- Well, look at the posts.
I would stab her.

42:06.667 --> 42:08.667
This has to all be connected somehow.

42:09.750 --> 42:10.750
- Maybe.

42:11.667 --> 42:13.500
Let me see if I can find her address.

42:14.458 --> 42:16.458
[typing]

42:17.458 --> 42:22.875
- Well, let's just regroup tomorrow
and do it. I gotta get home.

42:24.625 --> 42:25.625
- Get home?

42:25.625 --> 42:28.833
- Yeah, I just don't wanna freak out
my parents even more.

42:31.542 --> 42:33.542
I spent years training them
to stop worrying about me,

42:33.542 --> 42:35.500
I don't wanna screw it all up now.

42:35.500 --> 42:37.500
- Why do they worry about you?

42:38.500 --> 42:40.917
- I don't know, they just do.

42:40.917 --> 42:41.917
And I hate it.

42:43.042 --> 42:44.667
- Wa-- Hey, hey, hey, Cassidy?

42:46.375 --> 42:47.792
Are we cool?

42:48.500 --> 42:50.708
- Yeah, why wouldn't we be cool?

42:50.708 --> 42:54.917
- I couldn't tell from your comment
if you were, like, pissed off, or--

42:55.542 --> 42:57.583
- My comment on your video?

42:57.583 --> 42:59.667
I thought I just put "wow."

42:59.667 --> 43:04.667
- Well, yeah, but I... I couldn't tell
if you meant like "wow."

43:07.708 --> 43:10.333
- You know, in real life,
you are way different

43:10.333 --> 43:11.542
than you are in your channel.

43:12.208 --> 43:14.208
Thought you'd be way more, like, chill.

43:15.208 --> 43:16.292
- I am chill.

43:16.792 --> 43:18.792
- Hm.
- I am.

43:20.458 --> 43:24.083
- Look, okay, I just hadn't had
any time alone to relax

43:24.083 --> 43:25.250
and process all of this.

43:25.250 --> 43:26.375
That's something I need.

43:27.292 --> 43:28.917
I'm actually a really Zen-like person.

43:29.708 --> 43:30.708
- Really?

43:31.500 --> 43:33.125
You don't strike me as Zen-like at all.

43:33.500 --> 43:34.917
- Why not?

43:34.917 --> 43:38.750
- Dude, because... a Zen-like person
doesn't have to hide in their room

43:38.750 --> 43:40.708
and meditate every time
something goes wrong.

43:41.625 --> 43:44.625
A Zen-like person could be
in the middle of the most fucked up,

43:44.625 --> 43:47.833
insane situation ever
and still find inner peace.

43:48.708 --> 43:49.917
It's what Zen is.

43:57.542 --> 43:59.792
- That was Sarah.
They still haven't heard from her.

44:00.250 --> 44:01.417
- Well, I think it's time
to call the police.

44:01.417 --> 44:02.833
- Yeah.
[phone chimes]

44:07.458 --> 44:09.458
- Kamran, please just
go back downstairs, alright?

44:09.458 --> 44:10.667
Everything's gonna be fine.

44:18.208 --> 44:19.042
- Amir?

44:19.958 --> 44:20.792
- What?

44:24.833 --> 44:25.833
- Oh my god.

44:31.625 --> 44:33.042
- Where is this?
- Oh my god.

44:34.625 --> 44:36.625
[growling]

44:37.667 --> 44:39.667
♪ electronic music playing ♪

44:41.083 --> 44:43.083
[indiscernible chatter]

44:43.083 --> 44:45.083
[cheering, whistling]

44:46.292 --> 44:48.292
[typing]

44:53.542 --> 44:54.750
- Ughhh!

45:04.875 --> 45:05.875
[beep]

45:07.958 --> 45:10.333
[ringing]

45:10.333 --> 45:12.542
Please be online.
Please be online.

45:15.708 --> 45:16.917
<i>- Boy, are you in trouble.</i>

45:16.917 --> 45:19.917
<i>Mom and Dad just peeled out</i>
<i>of the driveway at full blast.</i>

45:19.917 --> 45:21.125
- What?! Do they know where I am?

45:21.625 --> 45:22.583
<i>- Sure seemed like it.</i>

45:23.167 --> 45:24.250
<i>Where are you anyway?</i>

45:24.250 --> 45:27.125
- Never mind.
Um... is the WiFi back on?

45:27.125 --> 45:28.708
I need your help finding somebody.

45:29.167 --> 45:31.875
<i>- Yeah, but Dad installed some</i>
<i>kind of monitoring software.</i>

45:31.875 --> 45:33.375
<i>Anything I do could set it off.</i>

45:33.375 --> 45:35.583
- Wait, they just left
you there by yourself?

45:35.583 --> 45:37.000
<i>- Yeah, so?</i>

45:37.000 --> 45:39.333
<i>I haven't seen the Grimcutty.</i>
<i>They don't worry about me.</i>

45:41.833 --> 45:44.667
- Yeah, they don't worry about you.

45:45.458 --> 45:46.542
<i>- Find who?</i>

45:46.542 --> 45:48.500
[typing]

45:48.500 --> 45:50.125
- I need to find out
where this woman lives.

45:53.083 --> 45:53.917
Can you do it?

45:54.708 --> 45:55.917
<i>- There are ways, but--</i>

45:56.792 --> 45:58.000
- What?

45:58.000 --> 45:59.458
<i>- This might set off Dad's thing.</i>

45:59.458 --> 46:00.875
<i>I don't wanna get in trouble.</i>

46:00.875 --> 46:02.875
[wind whooshing]

46:16.750 --> 46:19.750
♪ ominous music plays ♪

46:22.167 --> 46:23.583
<i>What the frick is wrong with you?</i>

46:23.583 --> 46:26.333
- Kamran, I don't know exactly
what's going on with me,

46:26.333 --> 46:28.542
but I can really use someone
to believe me right now.

46:29.333 --> 46:32.250
Please... I need your help.

46:33.875 --> 46:34.875
[sighs]

46:36.167 --> 46:38.708
<i>- Fine, I'll work on it.</i>

46:40.375 --> 46:41.167
- Thanks, stupid.

46:41.167 --> 46:42.458
- You're welcome, jerk.

46:42.458 --> 46:43.667
[call ends]

46:44.917 --> 46:47.917
♪ pop music playing ♪

46:50.458 --> 46:52.458
[typing]

47:02.208 --> 47:04.208
♪

47:07.208 --> 47:08.917
[tires screeching]

47:09.583 --> 47:11.542
- Oh my god.
- What?

47:11.792 --> 47:13.958
- She's posting about Grimcutty now.

47:13.958 --> 47:14.583
- What?!

47:15.833 --> 47:17.833
[gasps]
[snarls]

47:19.708 --> 47:21.792
- She's posting about Grimcutty, hurry!

47:21.792 --> 47:23.792
♪

47:35.000 --> 47:37.250
- Oh, hey, hey, look at that!

47:37.250 --> 47:38.875
- Huh?
- Look at that!

47:39.375 --> 47:41.417
PARTYGOER: Look at what?
ASHA: That!

47:41.417 --> 47:43.042
How can you not see that?!

47:46.750 --> 47:47.750
- Goddamnit.

47:47.750 --> 47:49.583
[tires screeching]

47:49.583 --> 47:51.417
[engine revving]

47:51.417 --> 47:52.333
[car honks]

47:55.208 --> 47:57.208
[gasping]

47:58.375 --> 48:00.292
[growls]

48:02.958 --> 48:04.583
[screams]

48:18.667 --> 48:21.667
♪ electronic music playing ♪

48:41.958 --> 48:43.750
- [screams] Help! Help!

48:43.750 --> 48:45.542
Please somebody help me!

48:45.542 --> 48:46.625
Help!

48:46.625 --> 48:48.667
[music stops]
Somebody! Anybody!

48:48.667 --> 48:49.792
[people booing]

48:49.792 --> 48:51.417
Help me!
[growls]

48:52.042 --> 48:53.417
Help! Anybody!

48:53.417 --> 48:54.792
LEAH:
Asha!

48:54.792 --> 48:57.083
- Somebody help me!

48:57.083 --> 49:00.083
[screaming]
LEAH: Asha!

49:01.042 --> 49:04.667
[cries]
- Asha! Asha!

49:05.667 --> 49:08.042
Drop the knife, Asha! Drop it, drop it!

49:09.750 --> 49:11.750
[crying]

49:12.875 --> 49:13.875
Let me see.

49:16.333 --> 49:17.333
God damn.

49:27.792 --> 49:28.792
- Did you see it?

49:32.708 --> 49:35.708
It was right there.
How did you not see it?

49:40.000 --> 49:42.208
- We're gonna get you the help
that you need, sweetheart, okay?

49:42.208 --> 49:43.000
I promise.

49:44.833 --> 49:46.083
AMIR:
The hell?

49:46.083 --> 49:47.917
Someone's using the WiFi in our house.

49:48.708 --> 49:50.042
Did you leave your laptop out?

49:50.667 --> 49:52.083
LEAH: Me?
- Yeah, you.

49:52.083 --> 49:55.333
- Uh, no. It's in the Detox Box
with everything else.

49:55.333 --> 49:56.667
- Well, then who the hell is this?

50:02.333 --> 50:03.542
What did you do?

50:03.875 --> 50:05.083
LEAH:
What did you do?

50:06.458 --> 50:09.458
Asha, tell us the truth,
what did you do?

50:12.875 --> 50:14.500
- It's not his fault.

50:14.500 --> 50:15.333
- Come on.

50:15.333 --> 50:16.625
ASHA:
I told him to do it.

50:20.750 --> 50:22.750
Mom, Dad, just calm down!

50:22.750 --> 50:24.167
- Seatbelt! Now!

50:38.375 --> 50:39.375
- Gotcha.

50:43.875 --> 50:45.875
[ringing]

50:48.333 --> 50:50.083
♪ ominous music playing ♪

50:53.542 --> 50:54.750
[ringing continues]

51:04.250 --> 51:05.708
[growls]

51:13.917 --> 51:14.917
AMIR:
Kamran!

51:17.250 --> 51:18.875
Oh my god, Kamran.

51:25.708 --> 51:26.917
- He's breathing.
- Oh god.

51:29.208 --> 51:30.833
Hey! Get back!

51:33.750 --> 51:34.750
LEAH:
Can you hear me, baby?

51:34.750 --> 51:35.792
- I'm gonna call 911.

51:39.500 --> 51:42.583
Uh, hi. Um, yeah, uh, my son,

51:42.583 --> 51:44.792
we just found him on the floor,
he-he's unconscious.

51:52.625 --> 51:54.625
[monitor beeping]

52:02.417 --> 52:03.250
[gasps]

52:03.250 --> 52:04.667
- That's it, careful, careful.

52:05.542 --> 52:07.542
You have to go slow
because the pain meds

52:07.542 --> 52:08.958
knocked you out pretty good.

52:19.083 --> 52:20.708
The doctors are hopeful.

52:21.250 --> 52:22.958
They're outside right now
talking to your dad.

52:22.958 --> 52:24.792
They, They say he could
wake up any minute.

52:28.083 --> 52:30.208
- Oh my god, I'm bleeding again.
There's blood.

52:30.208 --> 52:31.667
- No, no, no, it's fine.
Let me see.

52:32.333 --> 52:33.333
Stay put.

52:35.625 --> 52:37.625
You know what, I have to get somebody
to come change your bandages.

52:38.250 --> 52:39.667
And I'm actually gonna get you
some clean sheets

52:39.667 --> 52:41.333
and some blue pads
while I'm at it.

52:41.333 --> 52:42.542
You just stay put, okay?

52:45.208 --> 52:47.625
We made an appointment for you
for later this afternoon.

52:48.625 --> 52:49.917
With a psychiatrist.

52:52.292 --> 52:53.125
- It's not my fault.

52:54.958 --> 52:56.958
- 'Course it's not your fault.

52:56.958 --> 52:58.375
- It's what Dad thinks.

53:00.417 --> 53:03.625
- You know, he's, uh, he's--
Your dad's scared.

53:03.625 --> 53:07.458
So, he... he overreacted, that's all.

53:09.792 --> 53:10.792
I'll be right back.

53:12.958 --> 53:13.958
ASHA:
Mom?

53:16.792 --> 53:18.417
You've known me my whole life.

53:20.083 --> 53:22.500
I've never hurt myself before this.

53:22.500 --> 53:24.042
Just think about it,
it doesn't make any sense.

53:24.042 --> 53:26.917
- We saw you cutting yourself!
You were cutting yourself, Asha.

53:26.917 --> 53:29.125
What am I supposed to do with that?
You tell me.

53:31.625 --> 53:33.458
Let's let the psych handle it.

53:33.458 --> 53:35.458
I think that he's gonna help you
make sense of this, okay?

53:35.458 --> 53:36.458
I'll be right back.

53:38.208 --> 53:39.333
[door closes]

53:45.583 --> 53:47.583
♪

54:07.792 --> 54:09.417
- [cries] I'm sorry, Kamran.

54:12.167 --> 54:14.167
[sniffles, cries]

54:17.667 --> 54:19.667
♪

54:56.333 --> 55:01.167
PERSON: [over intercom]
<i>Sasha Beady, 4152. Sasha Beady, 4152.</i>

55:02.292 --> 55:03.500
- Mr. and Mrs. Johnston?

55:06.417 --> 55:07.625
Come with me, please.

55:18.500 --> 55:21.458
NEWS ANCHOR:
<i>New, disturbing reports</i>
<i>of teens gathering together</i>

55:21.458 --> 55:23.083
<i>to try the Grimcutty challenge,</i>

55:23.500 --> 55:24.958
<i>watch each other cut themselves,</i>

55:24.958 --> 55:28.667
<i>and even engage in bizarre</i>
<i>group cutting rituals.</i>

55:28.667 --> 55:30.250
[door opens]
<i>For more on this developing story,</i>

55:30.250 --> 55:31.875
<i>we wanna go now</i>
<i>to News Channel 8--</i>

55:36.458 --> 55:38.875
- Okay, I believe you now.

55:40.667 --> 55:41.625
- Where did it get you?

55:42.042 --> 55:43.458
- I was trying to crawl under the bed,

55:43.458 --> 55:46.042
and... it got me in the legs.

55:46.667 --> 55:47.667
Can't even walk.

55:48.208 --> 55:49.917
You know, when I asked you about the cuts,

55:49.917 --> 55:52.083
you could've just said
that Grimcutty's this

55:52.083 --> 55:54.750
real life huge fucking creature,
and it's gonna cut you.

55:55.208 --> 55:57.167
- When'd you see it?
- Last night.

55:57.875 --> 56:01.292
After my parents saw that video,
they, like, freaked out

56:01.292 --> 56:02.542
and sent me to my room.

56:04.250 --> 56:05.875
They were convinced I was suicidal.

56:08.208 --> 56:09.208
What happened to you?

56:10.625 --> 56:11.833
Wait, what are you even doing here?

56:12.292 --> 56:13.292
- I got the address.

56:13.792 --> 56:15.000
- Of the mommy blogger?

56:15.000 --> 56:17.417
- I was just on my way there.
I stole my mom's keys.

56:17.417 --> 56:19.167
- What, so you're just
gonna knock on her door

56:19.167 --> 56:21.958
and be like, "Oh, hi.
I'm a huge fan of your blog.

56:21.958 --> 56:25.250
Just happened to be in the neighborhood.
And by the way, are you totally insane?"

56:26.833 --> 56:28.042
- I have a theory.

56:29.583 --> 56:31.000
- Tell me.
[Asha sighs]

56:32.167 --> 56:35.292
- You just said when your parents saw
the video and freaked out,

56:35.292 --> 56:36.542
that's when it attacked you.

56:37.375 --> 56:40.583
And it di-- it didn't attack my brother
until my parents found out

56:40.583 --> 56:42.458
he was using a computer
and freaked out, too.

56:42.458 --> 56:45.500
It's, like, whenever their hysteria
about Grimcutty boils over,

56:45.500 --> 56:46.625
that's when it attacks.

56:47.583 --> 56:51.792
- So... what?
Our parents are controlling it?

56:52.208 --> 56:53.417
- Not on purpose.

56:55.000 --> 56:56.625
It's like they don't
know they're doing it.

56:57.875 --> 57:01.667
And they can't see it,
so when I try to tell them what I saw,

57:01.667 --> 57:04.500
it just makes them think I'm more crazy
and just makes them more hysterical.

57:05.500 --> 57:06.750
It's like a vicious cycle.

57:08.167 --> 57:10.208
- Okay, so how do we break the cycle?

57:12.458 --> 57:13.417
- I don't know.

57:15.167 --> 57:16.375
- Well, you need to figure it out soon.

57:16.375 --> 57:19.458
'Cause this psychiatrist
that I met with earlier,

57:20.250 --> 57:21.958
my parents are meeting
with them right now.

57:23.875 --> 57:27.792
So... if our parents freaking out
makes it stronger,

57:27.792 --> 57:30.958
then... I'm dead.

57:32.417 --> 57:35.500
♪

57:59.250 --> 58:00.458
- Oh shit.

58:06.542 --> 58:07.750
Shit.

58:10.625 --> 58:12.625
♪

58:19.417 --> 58:21.625
AMIR: Find anything on there?
- No.

58:22.708 --> 58:25.167
- Where's Asha?
LEAH: Um, [clears throat]

58:26.500 --> 58:29.333
the psych's office had an opening,

58:30.042 --> 58:32.167
so they were able
to take her in earlier.

58:32.167 --> 58:34.000
And she was feeling better, so.

58:37.208 --> 58:38.542
I was actually--
I was just waiting for you.

58:38.542 --> 58:39.625
What did the doctor say?

58:40.208 --> 58:41.167
- More of the same.

58:42.958 --> 58:44.708
He might wake up today. Might not.

58:45.583 --> 58:48.250
They've had a lot
of Grimcutty-related cases, so.

58:52.000 --> 58:55.083
You know, this could all just be
some kind of cyber-attack.

58:55.708 --> 58:57.000
I mean, they've tried it before.

58:57.583 --> 58:59.625
Use our networks to incite violence.

59:00.208 --> 59:02.167
I mean, anybody could
do it from anywhere.

59:03.083 --> 59:06.708
You know, aim it against a particular
community if you wanted, like ours.

59:08.500 --> 59:11.083
- Okay, I am, I'm gonna head back down.

59:11.083 --> 59:14.708
I'll, I'll let you know how, how,
how it goes after her appointment.

59:16.708 --> 59:18.708
♪

59:25.625 --> 59:26.875
Damnit, Asha.

59:27.417 --> 59:29.042
The hell are you into now?

59:38.000 --> 59:39.208
[handbrake creaks]

59:41.208 --> 59:44.208
♪ foreboding music playing ♪

59:54.208 --> 59:55.208
[doorbell rings]

1:00:01.917 --> 1:00:03.917
- Hi, can I help you?

1:00:04.958 --> 1:00:05.958
- Hi.

1:00:05.958 --> 1:00:07.083
Sorry to just show up like this,

1:00:07.083 --> 1:00:09.417
but I read your blog
and I was wondering

1:00:09.417 --> 1:00:11.625
if I could ask you
some questions about it.

1:00:13.375 --> 1:00:16.458
It's, It's for a class, and I didn't know
how else to contact you, so--

1:00:16.458 --> 1:00:17.708
- You could've just emailed me,

1:00:17.708 --> 1:00:19.708
but, uh, sure, what, what, what
do you wanna know?

1:00:21.667 --> 1:00:25.000
- Uh, well, I saw your
post about Grimcutty,

1:00:25.000 --> 1:00:27.750
and I was wondering--
- Sorry, I don't know what that is.

1:00:28.833 --> 1:00:32.000
- Uh, Grimcutty. The online challenge
thing you posted about.

1:00:32.542 --> 1:00:34.083
- I don't remember anything like that.

1:00:35.917 --> 1:00:38.333
- Oh, it's, uh, it's, like, a, um,
a challenge thing

1:00:38.958 --> 1:00:42.833
that's mak-- well, supposedly,
making kids cut themselves.

1:00:44.042 --> 1:00:47.583
And there... there was, like,
a rumor or something

1:00:48.250 --> 1:00:51.875
that, like, it made some kid,
like, stab his mom.

1:00:55.000 --> 1:00:57.417
[laughs]

1:00:59.458 --> 1:01:01.292
- I'm sorry, what, what did you say
your name was, honey?

1:01:01.833 --> 1:01:02.833
- Asha.

1:01:02.833 --> 1:01:05.250
- Asha, if I had a nickel for every time
I get asked about this.

1:01:07.958 --> 1:01:11.708
Look, the bottom line is that my family
had an accident a while ago

1:01:12.125 --> 1:01:14.417
and needless to say,
it's been blown way out of proportion,

1:01:14.417 --> 1:01:15.083
but it's fine.

1:01:15.083 --> 1:01:17.042
We're fine. Everything is fine. Really.

1:01:17.375 --> 1:01:19.583
- Okay. Well, are you sure
you haven't heard of Grimcutty?

1:01:20.458 --> 1:01:21.875
- Do your parents know that you're here?

1:01:21.875 --> 1:01:23.167
- Do you really not know
what's going on?

1:01:23.167 --> 1:01:24.000
- What do you mean?

1:01:24.417 --> 1:01:27.125
- Everyone in town is reading your blog
and following what it says.

1:01:27.125 --> 1:01:28.000
Like, religiously.

1:01:32.750 --> 1:01:33.750
- Huh.

1:01:35.000 --> 1:01:37.250
Well, I haven't, uh,
updated it in a while,

1:01:37.250 --> 1:01:41.250
but I... I'm very glad to hear
that people are connecting with it.

1:01:41.833 --> 1:01:43.333
Maybe you should go home.

1:01:43.333 --> 1:01:44.167
But you should email me--
- But--

1:01:44.167 --> 1:01:46.625
- and if I think of anything,
I will let you know, okay?

1:01:46.625 --> 1:01:47.458
Drive safe.

1:01:48.667 --> 1:01:49.667
[door closes]

1:02:17.583 --> 1:02:19.583
[leaves rustling]

1:02:30.542 --> 1:02:32.042
[exhales]

1:02:32.042 --> 1:02:34.042
[rustling]

1:02:49.833 --> 1:02:52.458
[indiscernible conversation]

1:02:52.458 --> 1:02:55.458
[muffled]
I know, it's for your own good, baby.

1:02:55.458 --> 1:02:56.667
No. Drink all of it.

1:02:59.333 --> 1:03:01.333
♪

1:03:21.167 --> 1:03:22.625
[clattering]

1:03:28.958 --> 1:03:30.958
♪

1:03:48.333 --> 1:03:50.333
♪

1:03:54.292 --> 1:03:56.292
[door creaking]

1:04:05.417 --> 1:04:07.417
[loud creaking]

1:04:10.375 --> 1:04:12.375
♪

1:05:09.000 --> 1:05:11.000
[door creaking]

1:05:15.625 --> 1:05:16.833
- [whispering] Hello?

1:05:40.458 --> 1:05:42.458
♪

1:05:54.958 --> 1:05:56.958
♪

1:06:04.958 --> 1:06:06.458
♪

1:06:07.125 --> 1:06:08.125
Oh my god.

1:06:08.708 --> 1:06:09.708
Oh my god.

1:06:10.500 --> 1:06:12.167
Hey. What happened to you?

1:06:13.167 --> 1:06:14.333
- Put me back.

1:06:14.750 --> 1:06:15.875
- What?

1:06:15.875 --> 1:06:18.500
- Lock me back in. She'll see you.

1:06:18.500 --> 1:06:19.708
- But I have to get you out of here.

1:06:19.708 --> 1:06:22.958
- No. I can't make Mom
worry about me.

1:06:22.958 --> 1:06:23.958
[gun cocks]

1:06:24.750 --> 1:06:26.000
- Stay calm, Asha.

1:06:27.250 --> 1:06:28.458
Just relax.

1:06:29.167 --> 1:06:31.917
Reach back with one hand,
grab your phone, and toss it to me.

1:06:34.000 --> 1:06:35.042
- I don't have a phone.

1:06:35.542 --> 1:06:38.000
- A girl your age leaving
your home without a phone?

1:06:38.875 --> 1:06:40.083
Think you better tell me the truth.

1:06:41.042 --> 1:06:43.042
- Detox Box, bitch!

1:06:44.500 --> 1:06:45.792
- Out into the hallway then.

1:06:47.958 --> 1:06:49.000
Now!

1:06:49.708 --> 1:06:52.042
Come on... oh.

1:06:53.125 --> 1:06:55.833
Are you sure you don't have a phone?

1:06:56.792 --> 1:06:58.500
- What did you do to him?
- Me?

1:06:59.292 --> 1:07:01.750
He did that to himself.
I'm just trying to protect him.

1:07:01.750 --> 1:07:04.375
[car approaching]

1:07:06.792 --> 1:07:07.833
[car door opens]

1:07:18.750 --> 1:07:20.250
[doorbell rings]

1:07:24.625 --> 1:07:26.375
- Um, oh, hi.

1:07:26.375 --> 1:07:27.625
- Are you looking
for your daughter by chance?

1:07:27.625 --> 1:07:30.542
- Yes, is sh--
ASHA: [shouting] Mom! Mom! I'm back here!

1:07:30.542 --> 1:07:31.750
- Just come, come in.
[sighs]

1:07:31.750 --> 1:07:32.750
Please, come in.
- I'm sorry.

1:07:32.750 --> 1:07:34.958
- She broke in, and I found her
in one of the back rooms

1:07:34.958 --> 1:07:36.542
and I had to lock her in real quick.

1:07:36.542 --> 1:07:38.625
I'm, I'm really sorry,
I just-- I didn't know what to do.
[Asha yelling]

1:07:38.625 --> 1:07:39.833
I was about to call the police.

1:07:39.833 --> 1:07:42.417
- Oh gosh. Please, no need.
I-I-I'll take it from here.

1:07:42.417 --> 1:07:43.542
I am so sorry about this.
- No worries.

1:07:43.542 --> 1:07:44.792
I'm just gonna unlock her real fast.

1:07:44.792 --> 1:07:46.917
I'm, I'm Melinda, by the way.
- Yes. Yes, yes, yes.

1:07:46.917 --> 1:07:49.167
I know. I read your blog.
ASHA: Mom, look out, she's got a gun!

1:07:49.917 --> 1:07:52.958
- Gosh, she just, she really
hasn't been herself lately,

1:07:52.958 --> 1:07:54.875
and I was worried she would
do something like this.

1:07:54.875 --> 1:07:56.250
I'm-- Again, I'm really, really sorry--

1:07:56.250 --> 1:07:58.458
- As long as you're sure that
you can handle her, I won't ask.

1:07:58.458 --> 1:07:59.417
LEAH:
Thank you so much.

1:07:59.417 --> 1:08:01.000
- Mom, don't listen to her,
she just pointed a gun at me!

1:08:01.000 --> 1:08:02.167
- Take it easy.

1:08:02.167 --> 1:08:04.875
- I'm serious! She's got her son
locked up in a closet upstairs!

1:08:04.875 --> 1:08:06.583
- Okay, calm down. We're gonna
talk about it in the car, okay?

1:08:06.583 --> 1:08:08.125
- No, wait, wait! We can't just
leave him here with her.

1:08:08.125 --> 1:08:09.583
She might kill him!
- Just calm down.

1:08:09.583 --> 1:08:11.083
- I'm not gonna let her
do that to him, okay?

1:08:11.083 --> 1:08:12.333
We have to get him out of here!

1:08:12.333 --> 1:08:13.708
She might kill him!
We have to save him!

1:08:13.708 --> 1:08:15.125
- Asha, stop it!
[slaps]

1:08:17.708 --> 1:08:19.708
♪

1:08:26.833 --> 1:08:28.667
I am so sorry about this.

1:08:30.750 --> 1:08:31.958
- Already forgotten.

1:08:33.333 --> 1:08:34.958
- We're gonna talk about it
when we get back to the hospital.

1:08:34.958 --> 1:08:36.833
- Mom, the same thing
that was happening to me,

1:08:36.833 --> 1:08:39.083
same thing's happening to him, only worse.

1:08:39.083 --> 1:08:40.708
- What's happening to you, Asha?

1:08:41.542 --> 1:08:42.375
- The Grimcutty.

1:08:42.750 --> 1:08:44.750
- No. No. No.
- The, The hysteria's feeding it!

1:08:45.250 --> 1:08:46.417
No, no, think about it!

1:08:46.417 --> 1:08:48.958
It didn't start attacking me
until you and Dad saw that photo!

1:08:48.958 --> 1:08:49.792
LEAH:
Ugh!

1:08:52.000 --> 1:08:54.000
♪

1:08:58.958 --> 1:09:00.792
- Mom, Mom, Mom, Mom, Mom,
chill for a second.

1:09:02.625 --> 1:09:03.958
Hey, will you please just calm down?

1:09:04.625 --> 1:09:06.000
- Calm down?

1:09:06.583 --> 1:09:08.917
After everything
that you have put us through,

1:09:08.917 --> 1:09:10.833
you want me to calm down?

1:09:10.833 --> 1:09:12.917
- I didn't mean to put
you through anything.

1:09:12.917 --> 1:09:14.292
- Of course, you didn't!

1:09:14.292 --> 1:09:18.250
Because that would require you
to think for one second

1:09:18.667 --> 1:09:21.167
how your behavior affects us!

1:09:21.167 --> 1:09:22.167
But you don't care!

1:09:22.167 --> 1:09:25.667
As long as we pay your phone bill,
as long as we cook your food,

1:09:25.667 --> 1:09:27.833
and buy you the latest
versions of everything,

1:09:27.833 --> 1:09:29.458
you could give a flying fuck!

1:09:29.458 --> 1:09:31.375
[shatters]

1:09:32.708 --> 1:09:34.708
[heavy breathing]

1:09:49.167 --> 1:09:50.000
Oh my god.

1:09:55.167 --> 1:09:56.458
Oh god.

1:09:58.542 --> 1:09:59.958
What the hell am I doing?

1:10:07.250 --> 1:10:09.542
Alright, just, um,

1:10:12.000 --> 1:10:13.500
take that in case anything happens,

1:10:14.250 --> 1:10:15.292
stay in the car,

1:10:16.292 --> 1:10:17.167
and I'll be right back.

1:10:17.167 --> 1:10:18.375
[door opens]
- Wait,

1:10:18.375 --> 1:10:20.208
Mom, Mom, what are you gonna do?

1:10:20.208 --> 1:10:21.292
- Stay in the car, Asha.

1:10:22.625 --> 1:10:24.625
- [sighs] Okay.

1:10:28.250 --> 1:10:29.333
- Car trouble?

1:10:29.333 --> 1:10:31.750
- No, you know, I just had one more thing,
if you don't mind.

1:10:31.750 --> 1:10:32.792
- Sure.

1:10:32.792 --> 1:10:35.875
- See, my daughter, she just said
something kind of crazy.

1:10:35.875 --> 1:10:38.417
She said something about
your son being starved

1:10:38.417 --> 1:10:40.125
and, and locked in a closet.

1:10:40.542 --> 1:10:43.000
So, I'm just trying to figure out
why she, why she would say that.

1:10:43.000 --> 1:10:44.958
- Your daughter's quite a character.

1:10:45.625 --> 1:10:49.125
- She is, I know, believe me I do know.
She's quite a character.

1:10:50.500 --> 1:10:52.125
Never known her to be a liar, though.

1:10:55.125 --> 1:10:58.417
- Well, I don't mean to presume,

1:10:58.958 --> 1:11:01.333
but sometimes people
with mental illness

1:11:01.333 --> 1:11:03.208
believe things to be true
even when they're not.

1:11:06.167 --> 1:11:07.375
- I also think I left my keys inside.

1:11:07.375 --> 1:11:09.125
- No. Excuse me, excuse me!

1:11:09.625 --> 1:11:12.750
This is ridiculous.
You need to leave right now.

1:11:13.375 --> 1:11:15.083
You know, she said another thing, too.

1:11:15.542 --> 1:11:17.792
She said that this whole
Grimcutty thing started with you.

1:11:17.792 --> 1:11:18.833
Is that true?

1:11:18.833 --> 1:11:20.792
- You need to leave my house right now,
or I'm gonna call the police.

1:11:20.792 --> 1:11:22.625
- Go ahead, call them please, I'll wait.

1:11:23.083 --> 1:11:25.083
Maybe they can check on your son,
make sure he's okay.

1:11:25.083 --> 1:11:25.792
[chuckles]

1:11:25.792 --> 1:11:29.042
This big collective freakout
about Grimcutty

1:11:29.042 --> 1:11:30.542
has put my family through hell,

1:11:30.542 --> 1:11:33.042
so I would like to know
where it came from.

1:11:33.042 --> 1:11:36.125
Did you make it up?
Just tell me and I will leave.
- My god.

1:11:39.333 --> 1:11:41.833
I didn't make it up,
I don't know who made it.

1:11:41.833 --> 1:11:45.250
I caught my son looking at it online,

1:11:45.250 --> 1:11:47.542
and the next thing I know,
he's cutting himself.

1:11:48.125 --> 1:11:49.208
And ever since then,

1:11:49.667 --> 1:11:51.833
I've been trying to keep
it out of my house

1:11:52.250 --> 1:11:54.958
and away from my child,
so I'd very much appreciate it

1:11:54.958 --> 1:11:57.250
if you would just stop talking about it.

1:11:57.250 --> 1:11:58.333
- Where did he find it?

1:11:58.333 --> 1:12:00.542
And what was he doing
when he found it? Do you know?

1:12:00.542 --> 1:12:02.042
- I, I told you that I don't
wanna talk about it.

1:12:02.042 --> 1:12:03.875
- Did he cut himself?
- Stop it!

1:12:03.875 --> 1:12:05.750
Stop it! I've cured him from that.

1:12:05.750 --> 1:12:07.917
There's nothing wrong with him now!

1:12:07.917 --> 1:12:09.125
There's nothing wrong with him!

1:12:09.583 --> 1:12:11.292
Oh god, there's nothing wrong with him.

1:12:11.292 --> 1:12:12.125
There's nothing wrong with him.

1:12:16.083 --> 1:12:17.833
[growling]

1:12:17.833 --> 1:12:19.292
[screams]

1:12:20.250 --> 1:12:23.083
No! No, no, no, no, no, no, no!

1:12:23.083 --> 1:12:24.625
There's nothing wrong with him.

1:12:24.625 --> 1:12:26.625
[screaming continues]

1:12:32.875 --> 1:12:35.292
♪

1:12:35.292 --> 1:12:37.292
[growls]

1:12:40.417 --> 1:12:42.083
[gun cocks]

1:12:42.083 --> 1:12:42.917
You bitch!

1:12:43.417 --> 1:12:45.542
I had it all under control!

1:12:45.542 --> 1:12:47.958
But you just couldn't shut up about it!

1:12:47.958 --> 1:12:48.792
[door opens]

1:12:49.583 --> 1:12:50.583
Stop!
- No!

1:12:56.417 --> 1:12:57.625
- Oh god.
- Mom!

1:12:58.208 --> 1:12:59.083
LEAH: Go!
ASHA: Mom!

1:12:59.083 --> 1:12:59.875
LEAH:
Go!

1:13:00.583 --> 1:13:02.167
- Stop! Stop!

1:13:02.792 --> 1:13:04.125
I know what's right for him!

1:13:04.792 --> 1:13:07.833
There's castle law in this state,
and I'm legally allowed to defend myself!

1:13:08.292 --> 1:13:10.667
I am the one who spread that photo around,

1:13:10.667 --> 1:13:12.792
and now I am the one
who has to contain it!

1:13:12.792 --> 1:13:14.167
[Brandon grunts]
Aah!

1:13:19.167 --> 1:13:22.417
Aah!
[thudding]

1:13:25.708 --> 1:13:27.708
♪

1:13:38.417 --> 1:13:39.417
LEAH:
Asha!

1:13:40.708 --> 1:13:41.917
Get the car quick.

1:13:43.083 --> 1:13:45.083
[monitor beeping]

1:13:49.792 --> 1:13:51.125
[exhales]

1:13:54.958 --> 1:13:55.958
[sniffles]

1:14:13.792 --> 1:14:15.792
[chair dragging]

1:14:24.167 --> 1:14:25.375
[computer beeps]

1:14:30.000 --> 1:14:32.000
♪

1:14:43.500 --> 1:14:44.500
Laura!

1:14:45.750 --> 1:14:47.625
- This is the kid?
LEAH: Over here. Yes, yes, please.

1:14:48.250 --> 1:14:49.958
Just be careful,
I could've sworn for a second

1:14:49.958 --> 1:14:51.208
he almost stopped breathing, so--

1:14:51.750 --> 1:14:54.250
LAURA:
We're gonna need intubation supplies

